PolySwell.descr: Factory Preset 01 Rich chords with a slow attack that ring out.  Press the expression pedal to slide up an octave

SparkArp.descr: Factory Preset 03 A light sweet arp with long sustain, this turns dark and machine like when the expression pedal is pushed down

MonoEcho.descr: Factory Preset 04 A space-age echo-forward sounds that, as the pedal goes down, drops 2 octaves and gets heavily filtered

PolyGlide.descr: Factory Preset 05 A rich slide into a sustained chord, as the pedal goes down the detune is increased adding some sharpness to the sound

DarkArp.descr: Factory Preset 06 Tuned tom-toms beat out a rich evening tone, things turn into computer love as the pedal goes down

MonoTyrell.descr: Factory Preset 07 Metalic sinister insects buzzing at the edge of control, press the pedal for dark filtered demons

BellLab.descr: Factory Preset 09 Dark and ominous bells for your horror movie soundtrack

Woodwind.descr: Factory Preset 10 An echo heavy woodwind plays in the forest

RileyCurve.descr: Factory Preset 11 A sci-fi hero on the run with infinite sustain, our hero see's opportuity as the pedal goes down

PondBass.descr: Factory Preset 12 A deep bass with a slow attack

Starland.descr: Factory Preset 13 Ths flying saucer takes off, runs it to trouble and lands.  Press the pedal to succesfuly hover.

FormantRing.descr: Factory Preset 14 The robot phones it in.  Bad news, HAL is not opening the pod bay doors.

LinkArp.descr: Factory Preset 15 Metalic tines play a staccato arpeggio, like a robot playing a steel drum. Push the pedal to drop and stretch.

ExpSweep.descr: Factory Preset 16 We lay our heads down to rest as IO and Europa pass overhead

AA0 Click me.descr: Click on a patch name in this list to preview the sound

AA1 Drag to Preset.descr: Click and Drag a Patch Name to a Preset button on the left to store the preset in one of Enzo's 16 preset slots

AA2 Drag to Disk.descr: Drag to the disk icon below,  to export the patch with name and description to a file to share with others that have this program

AA3 Drag to SYX.descr: Drag to SYX below, to export the patch to a sysex file to share with others

AA4 Drag to the Trash.descr: Drag a patch name to the trashcan on the lower right to remove a patch from the library

AA5 Use Search.descr: Use the search box below to find patches.  Search sorts the patches in search order, try typing 'poly' or 'factory' in the search box

AA6 Globals.descr: Look in the Settings menu to adjust the Enzo Global Settings

AA7 Navigate.descr: Click on the bit script E icon in the upper left corner to switch between the editor and the librarian, try it now!

AA8 Enough!.descr: Enough directions, drag all the direction patches to the trash and explore on your own

Light Pad.descr: Strum chords and light pad fills in the sound, pressing the pedal brings up the porto for added movement

Funky Quackery.descr: The quack of the envelope filter with delay

ArpChimes.descr: Bell like synth tones, in a slower moving soothing arp

OB-X.descr: Reminds me of the Oberheim OB-X #LordRadish

LoooongSwell.descr: Long deep throbbing swell, organ like higher frequency detuned modulation #LordRadish

Ripples.descr: Swell with a slight pulse in spots

A Tense Calm.descr: Relaxed, but dark, clear guitar with a dark pad  #LordRadish

Thats Just Swell.descr: Swell in Dry mode, little bit of echo.  #LordRadish

Octave Down Whammy.descr: Press the toe down to drop an octave

Octave Up Whammy.descr: Press the toe down to go up an octave, a touch of compression for increased sustain

Low Pass Pedal.descr: Press the pedal to sweep the cutoff on the LP filter

Synth Wah Sweep.descr: Sweep the pedal across the cut-off of the Ladder BP

Bright poly pad.descr: a bright pad with motion from the portamento

Two Octave Up Whammy.descr: Press the pedal down to jump up 2 octaves

PolyRing.descr: Factory Preset 02 An accordion like tone.  The envelope modulates the ring modulator to a tremelo that starts fast and slows
